    <title>How to Embed a Video Tutorial</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>How to Embed a Video into Your Website</h1>

    <h2>Step 1: Find a Video</h2>
    <p>Go to a video platform like YouTube and select the video you want to embed.</p>
    <img src="images/step1.png" alt="Screenshot of video selection">

    <h2>Step 2: Click the Share Button</h2>
    <p>Under the video, click the 'Share' button to see sharing options.</p>
    <img src="images/step2.png" alt="Screenshot of Share button">

    <h2>Step 3: Select 'Embed'</h2>
    <p>Choose the 'Embed' option from the sharing menu.</p>
    <img src="images/step3.png" alt="Screenshot of Embed option">

    <h2>Step 4: Copy the Embed Code</h2>
    <p>Copy the code provided in the box.</p>
    <img src="images/step4.png" alt="Screenshot of embed code">

    <h2>Step 5: Paste the Code into Your HTML</h2>
    <p>Open your HTML file and paste the embed code where you want the video to appear.</p>
    <img src="images/step5.png" alt="Screenshot of HTML file with code">

    <h2>Final Result: Embedded Video</h2>
    <p>Your video should now appear like this:</p>
    <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/dQw4w9WgXcQ" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>
</body>
</html>
